4. Cloud Service Models

Cloud services are categorized into three primary models, and AWS provides offerings in all three:
IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)- You get raw computing resources over the internet.

    You manage: OS, middleware, runtime, data, applications.
    AWS manages: Hardware, networking, virtualization.
    Example: Amazon EC2, Amazon VPC, Amazon EBS

PaaS (Platform as a Service) - Provides a platform to develop, run, and manage applications without managing the underlying infrastructure.
    
    You just focus on the application code.
    Example: AWS Elastic Beanstalk, AWS Lambda, AWS AppRunner

SaaS (Software as a Service) - Fully managed applications delivered via the cloud.

    End-users consume the service; no management of infrastructure or platform.
    Example: Amazon Chime (communications), AWS QuickSight (BI tool)


